    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Lynn Hirschberg highlights the contradictions inherent in Bette Midler's righteous indignation over indecent billboards and Bill Clinton's behavior. But she leaves unchallenged Midler's casual assertion that she was upset because she had to cross a picket line to get to her ''upfront'' at Carnegie Hall. What happened to Midler's high-minded moralizing on that occasion?</p>
        <p>Karen Bennett  New York</p>
      </block>
